concise_prompt:
Draw a horizontal row of 5 square-grid panels, each with a 4x4 grid and labeled (A) through (E) below. In each panel, include a thick black orthogonal path, a small light-gray cartoon dog icon, and a small light-gray bone icon. Position the dog and bone icons and draw the paths as follows: 
(A) dog upper-left, bone lower-right, path descends in steps; 
(B) dog middle-left, bone upper-right, path dips then rises; 
(C) dog lower-middle, bone upper-left, path forms a boxy step; 
(D) dog lower-left, bone upper-right, path zigzags upward; 
(E) dog upper-left, bone lower-right, path descends in steps.

Draw a 5x5 grid with a shark, rhino, ghost, frog, and flower icon in each cell, following the pattern: 
Row 1: shark, rhino, ghost, flower, frog; 
Row 2: flower, frog, empty, empty, ghost; 
Row 3: rhino, ghost, flower, frog, shark; 
Row 4: frog, shark, empty, question mark, flower; 
Row 5: ghost, flower, frog, shark, rhino. 
Below the grid, include individual images of each icon and a row of answer choices labeled (A) ghost, (B) shark, (C) frog, (D) rhino, (E) flower.

Draw a diagram with 5 horizontal 2x4 grids labeled A, B, C, D, and E. Each grid contains 8 cells with uppercase letters: 
A: K A, N O, O G, R A; 
B: N G, A A, K R, O O; 
C: O O, K R, A A, G N; 
D: K A, N G, O O, R A; 
E: K O, A O, R N, A G. 
Place each label to the left of its grid.

question:
Christopher has made a building out of blocks. The grid on the right shows the number of blocks in each part of the building, when viewed from above. Which of the following gives the view you see when you look at Christopher's building from the front?
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|l|l|}
\hline 4 & 2 & 3 & 2 \\
\hline 3 & 3 & 1 & 2 \\
\hline 2 & 1 & 3 & 1 \\
\hline 1 & 2 & 1 & 2 \\
\hline \multicolumn{4}{|c|}{ front }
\end{tabular}
